==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Grunter
<hw>Grunt"er</hw> <pr>(gr⟦ucr⟧nt"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>One who, or that which, grunts; specifically, a
hog.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Bristled grunters.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Tennyson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of several American marine
fishes. See <er>Sea robin</er>, and <er>Grunt</er>, <pos>n.</pos>,
2.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Brass Founding)</fld> <def>A hook used in lifting a
crucible.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gruntingly</ent>⟦br⟧
